The paper deals with the problem of revenue maximization in auctions, which is a classic topic in game theory and mechanism design (cs.GT). The problem involves designing a mechanism that is computationally efficient, Bayesian Incentive Compatible, ex-post Individually Rational, and ex-post budget respecting, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the prior distribution over bidder values and budgets, which is a common theme in the sub-field of economics and computation (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses a black-box reduction from mechanism to algorithm design, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
